
###screenshot-script###

# Keyboard shortcut example
# Append this to your sxhkdrc (the config file for simple x hotkey daemon)
# printsrc by itself takes a fullscreen screenshot,
# + shift takes one with rectangle select
# + ctrl takes one of the focused window
# + alt takes one of a selected window with a rectangle select
# Combine any of those with
#     + super (a.k.a. windows key)
#     to save to ~/Pictures/screenshots instead of the clipboard.

Print + {_,shift,ctrl,alt} + {_,super}
	shot -l {full,rect,focus,rect_in_win} {'',-s ~/Pictures/screenshots}

